msgctxt "sn35.236:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.236:0.2"
msgid "18. Samuddavagga "
msgstr "18. The Ocean "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 236. Paṭhamahatthapādopamasutta → hatthapādūpamasuttaṃ (bj) | hatthapādupamā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.236:0.3"
msgid "236. Paṭhamahatthapādopamasutta "
msgstr "236. The Simile of Hands and Feet (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.236:1.1"
msgid "“Hatthesu, bhikkhave, sati ādānanikkhepanaṃ paññāyati; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when there are hands, picking up and putting down are found. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:1.2"
msgid "pādesu sati abhikkamapaṭikkamo paññāyati; "
msgstr "When there are feet, coming and going are found. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:1.3"
msgid "pabbesu sati samiñjanapasāraṇaṃ paññāyati; "
msgstr "When there are joints, contracting and extending are found. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:1.4"
msgid "kucchismiṃ sati jighacchā pipāsā paññāyati. "
msgstr "When there’s a belly, hunger and thirst are found. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.236:1.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, cakkhusmiṃ sati cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "In the same way, when there’s an eye, pleasure and pain arise internally conditioned by eye contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:1.6"
msgid "jivhāya sati jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "When there’s an ear … nose … tongue … body … "

msgctxt "sn35.236:1.7"
msgid "manasmiṃ sati manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhaṃ … pe …. "
msgstr "mind, pleasure and pain arise internally conditioned by mind contact. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.172, sc2
msgctxt "sn35.236:2.1"
msgid "Hatthesu, bhikkhave, asati ādānanikkhepanaṃ na paññāyati; "
msgstr "When there are no hands, picking up and putting down aren’t found. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:2.2"
msgid "pādesu asati abhikkamapaṭikkamo na paññāyati; "
msgstr "When there are no feet, coming and going aren’t found. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:2.3"
msgid "pabbesu asati samiñjanapasāraṇaṃ na paññāyati; "
msgstr "When there are no joints, contracting and extending aren’t found. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:2.4"
msgid "kucchismiṃ asati jighacchā pipāsā na paññāyati. "
msgstr "When there’s no belly, hunger and thirst aren’t found. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.236:2.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, cakkhusmiṃ asati cakkhusamphassapaccayā nuppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "In the same way, when there’s no eye, pleasure and pain don’t arise internally conditioned by eye contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.236:2.6"
msgid "jivhāya asati jivhāsamphassapaccayā nuppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "When there’s no ear … nose … tongue … body … "

msgctxt "sn35.236:2.7"
msgid "manasmiṃ asati manosamphassapaccayā nuppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhaṃ dukkhan”ti. "
msgstr "mind, pleasure and pain don’t arise internally conditioned by mind contact.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.236:2.8"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

